        <title>What is a data breach?</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>A data breach happend when <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au/privacy/your-privacy-rights/your-personal-information/what-is-personal-information"> personal information</a> is accessed,disclosed without authorisation, or is lost. For example,when:</p><br><br>
            <ul>
                <li> a USB or mobile phone that holds a individual's personal information is stolen</li>
                <li> a database containing personal information is hacked</li>
                <li> someone's personal information is sent to the wrong person</li>
            </ul>
            <br><br>
        <p>A data breach can harm an individual whose personal information is affected. They can, for example, suffer distress or financial loss.<br><br>
            There are <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au/privacy/your-privacy-rights/your-personal-information/what-is-personal-information"> things you can do to reduce your risk of harm. And, there's help available if you suffer distress.<br><br>
            </p>
    </body>
